{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.28",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 28 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:1",
      "text": "He that seeketh to revenge himself, shall find vengeance from the Lord, and he will surely keep his sins in remembrance.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:2",
      "text": "Forgive thy neighbour if he hath hurt thee: and then shall thy sins be forgiven to thee when thou prayest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:3",
      "text": "Man to man reserveth anger, and doth he seek remedy of God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:4",
      "text": "He hath no mercy on a man like himself, and doth he entreat for his own sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:5",
      "text": "He that is but flesh, nourisheth anger, and doth he ask forgiveness of God? who shall obtain pardon for his sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:6",
      "text": "Remember thy last things, and let enmity cease:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:7",
      "text": "For corruption and death hang over in his commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:8",
      "text": "Remember the fear of God, and be not angry with thy neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:9",
      "text": "Remember the covenant of the most High, and overlook the ignorance of thy neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:10",
      "text": "Refrain from strife, and thou shalt diminish thy sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:11",
      "text": "For a passionate man kindleth strife, and a sinful man will trouble his friends, and bring in debate in the midst of them that are at peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:12",
      "text": "For as the wood of the forest is, so the fire burneth, and as a man's strength is, so shall his anger be, and according to his riches he shall increase his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:13",
      "text": "A hasty contention kindleth a fire and a hasty quarrel sheddeth blood and a tongue that beareth witness bringeth death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:14",
      "text": "If thou blow the spark, it shall burn as a fire: and if thou spit upon it, it shall be quenched: both come out of the mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:15",
      "text": "The whisperer and the double tongue is accursed: for he hath troubled many that were at peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:16",
      "text": "The tongue of a third person hath disquieted many, and scattered them from nation to nation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:17",
      "text": "It hath destroyed the strong cities of the rich, and hath overthrown the houses of great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:18",
      "text": "It hath cut in pieces the forces of people, and undone strong nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:19",
      "text": "The tongue of a third person hath cast out valiant women, and deprived them of their labours.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:20",
      "text": "He that hearkeneth to it, shall never have rest, neither shall he have a friend in whom he may repose.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:21",
      "text": "The stroke of a whip maketh a blue mark: but the stroke of the tongue will break the bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:22",
      "text": "Many have fallen by the edge of the sword, but not so many as have perished by their own tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:23",
      "text": "Blessed is he that is defended from a wicked tongue, that hath not passed into the wrath thereof, and that hath not drawn the yoke thereof, and hath not been bound in its bands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:24",
      "text": "For its yoke is a yoke of iron: and its bands are bands of brass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:25",
      "text": "The death thereof is a most evil death: and hell is preferable to it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:26",
      "text": "Its continuance shall not be for a long time, but it shall possess the ways of the unjust: and the just shall not be burnt with its flame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:27",
      "text": "They that forsake God shall fall into it, and it shall burn in them, and shall not be quenched, and it shall be sent upon them as a lion, and as a leopard it shall tear them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:28",
      "text": "Hedge in thy ears with thorns, hear not a wicked tongue, and make doors and bars to thy mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:29",
      "text": "Melt down thy gold and silver, and make a balance for thy words, and a just bridle for thy mouth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.28.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:30",
      "text": "And take heed lest thou slip with thy tongue, and fall in the sight of thy enemies who lie in wait for thee, and thy fall be incurable unto death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
